.TH "pci_refresh_power_state" 9 "pci_refresh_power_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_refresh_power_state \- Refresh the given device's power state data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pci_refresh_power_state
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Target PCI device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Ask the platform to refresh the devices power state information and invoke
\fBpci_update_current_state\fP to update its current PCI power state.
